Frame is distinctive Astra five screw, with yoke retention screw and four screw side plate. Overall length is 8 3/8 inches by 5 1/4 inches height. Weight empty is 37 1/2 ounces, with center of gravity at the trigger. Finish is blued steel, with worn case colored hammer and trigger. Grips are Jordan type, press checkered lateral walnut, with nickel plated factory medallions, and with worn semi gloss finish. They will accommodate a 10A or 586A Speedloader well enough. Surface detractions on this Astra Police model are minimal to moderate, principally edge wear and finish wear to the right grip panel. We rate it as Very Good, 75 to 80 percent vicinity by my estimate. Bore, cylinder chambers and mechanism are all bright and clean. Blast effect to the top strap underside above the forcing cone is minimal, and cylinder face carbon is minimal. Cylinder times correctly in all six positions both double and single action, with hammer movement to spare. It has no lateral play whatsoever with the trigger fully depressed. Cylinder face to forcing cone gap measures .005 to .006. Double action trigger pull is smooth 11 pound vicinity, with crisp 4 pound vicinity single action pull. I estimate this revolver has been fired fewer than 500 times, no rounds at all for an Astra. From its PMV Marking, this Astra served with Airport Security at the Margarita Airport in Venezuela.
